replies.bodyText:
@pedroigor Sure, this is not safe. This is testsuite-only authenticator, which is not intended to be ever used in production. I've used authenticator just to be able to test this for the OAuth2 DirectGrant, as the Docker protocol automated tests don't work.
As you pointed, in case of the docker protocol, it is currently hardcoded - the note is set in the DockerEndpoint class. Other protocols (OIDC, SAML) currently don't have support for transient session in this PR - with the only exception of the testsuite, which have this SetClientNoteAuthenticator .
Do you think that we need authenticator to be added to the main codebase to be able to have transient sessions per flow? I can think that OAuth2 Resource Owner Password Credentials Grant (Direct Grant) in some cases doesn't need user session at all. AFAIK Sometimes people use DirectGrant just for the single authentication to some CLI app and never need to refresh or introspect tokens etc. Not sure if this is useful also for some other protocols - like for example SAML ECP? WDYT?
